-- Centrica Names Mastercard’s Haythornthwaite as Chairman
-- B y   N i d a a   B a k h s h
-- 2013-10-04T17:54:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-04/centrica-names-mastercard-s-haythornthwaite-as-chairman.html
Centrica Plc (CNA) , the largest energy
supplier to U.K. households and owner of British Gas, appointed
Richard Haythornthwaite as non-executive chairman effective Jan.
1. He succeeds  Roger Carr .  Haythornthwaite, 56, is chairman of Mastercard Inc.,
beginning his career as a geologist at BP Plc, the Windsor,
England-based company said today in a statement. He worked at
Europe’s second-biggest oil company for 17 years before joining
Premier Oil Plc and was former chairman of Network Rail Ltd.  He chairs Southbank Centre and was chief executive officer
at the industrial technology company Invensys Plc, according to
the statement. He studied at Oxford University, it said.  Haythornthwaite will join the board of Centrica as a non-executive director on Oct. 14. Carr is stepping down from
Centrica on Dec. 31 to become chairman of the defense contractor
BAE Systems Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nidaa Bakhsh in London at 
